PhexTask{#order:4,#uuid:UUID['5c323b610cb50d00b4d8f7cc0256805d'],#title:'Lights Out',#description:'# Lights Out game \r\r## The application\r\rLightsOutGame is a small graphical application that can be launched via `LightsOutGame class >> #open` (click on it).\r\r* Run the application by executing this method (clic on the play button near the method name).\r\rYou should see the following application:\r\r![Lights out game](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Pharo-XP-Tools/xp-free-resources/main/ocd/lights-out-game.png)\r\rIn this game, each tile represents a light bulb initially switched off. \rClicking on a tile will toggle it and its immediate neighbors, as illustrated below.\r\r![Lights out game, toggled tiles](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Pharo-XP-Tools/xp-free-resources/main/ocd/lights-out-game-toggles.png)\r\rTo win the game, a player must switch on all the lights in a minimal amount of actions.\r\r## The problem\r\rUnfortunately, there is a bug. As shown in the screenshot below, one light bulb located at one of the corners cannot be switched on. \r\r![Lights out game, bug](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Pharo-XP-Tools/xp-free-resources/main/ocd/lights-out-game-bug.png)\r\rEach time the game is launched, the bug appears in a new corner.\r\r## Your task\r\r* Understand why there is a light that cannot be switched on.\r* Fix the bug. Identify and delete the method responsible for this behavior.\r\rTo help you, you can inspect any tile/light by performing a right-click on it. This action will open an inspector on that tile/light.\r\r**Beware:** this is a graphical application, and putting breakpoints in the display system (e.g., in the Morph class) might freeze your system.\r',#contents:'# Lights Out game \r\r## The application\r\rLightsOutGame is a small graphical application that can be launched via `LightsOutGame class >> #open` (click on it).\r\r* Run the application by executing this method (clic on the play button near the method name).\r\rYou should see the following application:\r\r![Lights out game](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Pharo-XP-Tools/xp-free-resources/main/ocd/lights-out-game.png)\r\rIn this game, each tile represents a light bulb initially switched off. \rClicking on a tile will toggle it and its immediate neighbors, as illustrated below.\r\r![Lights out game, toggled tiles](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Pharo-XP-Tools/xp-free-resources/main/ocd/lights-out-game-toggles.png)\r\rTo win the game, a player must switch on all the lights in a minimal amount of actions.\r\r## The problem\r\rUnfortunately, there is a bug. As shown in the screenshot below, one light bulb located at one of the corners cannot be switched on. \r\r![Lights out game, bug](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Pharo-XP-Tools/xp-free-resources/main/ocd/lights-out-game-bug.png)\r\rEach time the game is launched, the bug appears in a new corner.\r\r## Your task\r\r* Understand why there is a light that cannot be switched on.\r* Fix the bug. Identify and delete the method responsible for this behavior.\r\rTo help you, you can inspect any tile/light by performing a right-click on it. This action will open an inspector on that tile/light.\r\r**Beware:** this is a graphical application, and putting breakpoints in the display system (e.g., in the Morph class) might freeze your system.\r',#started:false,#finished:false,#requiresAnswer:true,#requiredAnswer:'Explain why one of the corner switches cannot be switched on, and how you fixed that.',#survey:UUID['7ed93a610cb50d00b4d096bf0256805d']}